# Keep host-only / build artefacts out of the Fly Docker context.
# We CAN'T exclude workspace directories themselves (pnpm needs them
# present for `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` to resolve workspace:*
# protocol entries in the lockfile). We only strip their build outputs
# and host-side caches.

# Host-side build artefacts (rebuilt inside the image)
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Tests / coverage / native build outputs
**/coverage
**/.vitest-cache
apps/mobile/ios
apps/mobile/android
apps/mobile/.expo
apps/mobile/.expo-shared

# Astro / Next build caches
apps/marketing/.astro
apps/marketing/.wrangler
apps/docs/.next

# Editor / OS / VCS
.git
.github
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Env files (Fly uses real secrets via `fly secrets set`)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.deploy.example

# Misc
README.md
